FT  08 MAY 92 / International Company News: TWA reduces operating loss
TRANS World Airlines, the bankrupt carrier, posted another operating loss in
March, although the deficit was sharply reduced from the losses seen in the
first two months of the year, writes Nikki Tait.
According to documents filed with the bankruptcy court, TWA made an
operating loss of Dollars 15.1m in March, against a Dollars 49.3m deficit in
February and a Dollars 34.1m loss in January.
